Text.Value: We cannot win. We must aid in building these vargh'kron.
All right, I'll help. Where are your families?
Don't get upset - get revenge.
Who I am doesn't matter - I'm here to destroy the Foundry.
The Foundry was built to withstand the power of a hundred Wild Magic sorcerers.
But I do have to inform them. Your very presence here imperils us all.
Yes! Let's make these bastards suffer.
Narn'guth kree'shav da'lor.

EditorData.NodeContext: Narn'guth kree'shav da'lor. (naan-guff kree'shuv dah-lore) 'you don't belong here'

Text.Value: I don't have time for this - die already.
A grim solution, but one that I may agree with if your understanding of the situation were correct.
Come. Let's take this place down.
The destruction I can handle. I have a runepowder bomb.
I created the Neurocitor that controls the Steel Watch, and I made sure I had a means to disable it if I ever had the freedom to do so.
The collars are not only equipped with explosives, there is also a mechanism that alerts the overseers if they're removed.
The Steel Watch needs to be destroyed, and the Foundry along with it.
I'm here for entertainment - and it's been quite the show so far.
Hold here a moment. I'll be back.
Keep searching. We must find them - please.
Tharr'dakz. Fargh'nul kreth'nar da'droth. My daughter. Sweet Obelia, what have they done to you?

EditorData.NodeContext: Far-DACKS. Farg-NULL kreff-narr DAH-droff.   (Those aresholes. They killed my family)

Text.Value: Believe me or don't - I care not. But Gond kept me alive for a reason.
I'll kill all the overseers.
Runepowder? Gond's hammer, where did you find such a thing?
It's selfish to value your families more than an entire city.
Have you found them - our families?
I will pray for you. My daughter...her name is Obelia.

EditorData.NodeContext: love in his voice at the mention of his daughter

Text.Value: Before any of them can press a button in the palm of their hands? You may be quick, but nobody is that quick.
Gond spare us all.
I'm here to free you.
Unfortunately, we are not the only ones threatened by the collars, or we would have laid down our tools, and rebelled against our oppressors already.
Don't you think I know that? We're no cowards. We talked about revolting. We know what these Watchers are for.
Take me to it. I will disable the Steel Watch - and end this perversion of Gondian ideals.
There's always a way. Will you fight back if I free your families?
Our families are held elsewhere. The overseers need only activate those contraptions they hold, and they suffer the consequences of our actions too.
That makes sense.
Get me close enough to the central mechanism, and I can shut down the whole foundry. But first, our families must be safe.
Maybe. But it would be unnatural to feel otherwise.
One of us may be able to save themselves, but it would be at the expense of everyone else. We can't risk it.
Leave.
We need to move. The Neurocitor lies in the depths of the Foundry - and I have no doubt more than Banites await us.
Even if we did somehow unshackle our collars simultaneously, and overthrow our oppressors, there would be consequences.
Rise up in unison - they can't stop you all.
Runepowder? Did Wulbren send you?

EditorData.NodeContext: surprised, thought player was an ally but now fears they've been led astray by wulbren

Text.Value: Gond, light the path and grant us your wisdom.
Vargh'kron.
The Steel Watch must be destroyed, and the Foundry with it.
Blek'ith! Why?
No. Not without a fight.
In its depths, however, lies the Neurocitor - the nerve centre of the Steel Watch.
I don't know where they are. But some of the overseers must - you'll have to infiltrate deeper into the Foundry.
I have a runepowder bomb, and I intend to destroy this facility with it, no matter the cost.
What? Go away.
But it was a lie. They used a Motivator, probably laughed as collars activated - burning my friends, my family, from the inside out.
The Steel Watchers are tools of oppression - building them makes you complicit with the oppressors.
I'm [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53] - I'm here to take down the Steel Watch.
I know this place better than anyone - better than the Gondians even. I could help you destroy it, if I knew our families were safe.
Gond'kul, aye! Even more - I'd help you destroy this place.

EditorData.NodeContext: GOND-cull (by Gond), shocked, surprised, hopeful. Player has offered to help

Text.Value: With what I have planned, they will do more than suffer.
Leave, I beg of you. A Motivator is all that stands between my daughter and an agonising death.
But my daughter is among those they took away. I've no choice. And neither do the others.
There is little time - take me to the Neurocitor.
The overseers - they have a contraption. When triggered, it will kill everyone who wears a collar.
What is going on here?
My fellow Gondians are likely already dead. Cut down any Banites you see - they've earned their fate.
The Overseers must have used a Motivator. Bastards probably laughed as collars activated - burning my friends, my family, from the inside out.
I don't think a 'god' saved you. Maybe it just malfunctioned?
I have a runepowder bomb. I just need a target.
You've tormented me enough - leave me.

EditorData.logicalname: knows how to disable steel watch

Text.Value: Nothing yet.
All except me. Gond must have intervened - but why save me? Why is my life worth more than my daughter's?
I warned you - I warned you of the consequences, yet you had to interfere!
Gond'ral thra'kazhul nesh. May Gond be with you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Gond-rahl FRA-kazz-hool nesh. (may Gond be with you). Knows he's putting immense trust in the player.

Text.Value: If it were only our lives on the line, we'd have rebelled long ago.
If I tell you, won't you go running to the guards?
I'm in - just tell me how.
You underestimate the enemy. The overseers, they are glix'bran rak'tharr.
It's worth the risk - worst case scenario, you die fighting.
If everyone who wears a collar is helping to build the Steel Watch, killing you all may be a good thing.
The Banites must have a way of getting to and from the prison. I suggest you search the docks.
It's too late. The Banites collared us like dogs, locked our families away - promised us freedom if we followed their every command.
Your presence imperils us all. If any of us attempts to escape, our kin will die.
I'm here to end the Steel Watch - and that means any Gondians, too.
Just make sure you don't get caught. If they raise the alarm, they'll trigger the collars.
Help us and I promise we'll help you. You won't need something as drastic as runepowder to bring this place down. I know a way.
Look - Wulbren is no friend of the Gondians. He's a piece of frenk'vol. I don't know what poison he put in your mind, but we are good people in a bad place.

EditorData.NodeContext: frenk (friend with a 'k' instead of a 'd') VOL (shit). Determined to show player that wulbren is bad news (wulrebn really is)

Text.Value: I don't need freedom. I want vengeance.
My daughter is dead, they're all dead - because of you!
Perhaps the god of invention has a plan for you?
Hurry.
I thought you were the cure - our salvation. I had hope.

EditorData.logicalname: iron throne destroyed and asked help

Text.Value: Your nervous gait betrays your presence, stranger. You don't belong here. Who are you?
Where are your families being held?
If I cannot be my fellow Gondians' saviour - then I shall be their avenger.
This is nothing to do with me.
Can't you remove the collars?
The Banites. They collared us like dogs, locked our families away - promised us freedom if we followed their every command.
Sorry, but I need to stop the Steel Watch now.
Follow me to the neurocitor. I will show you how to overload it, and to shut down the Steel Watch forever.
How do you intend to help me?
All right, I'll help. Where are your families?
If you knew the truth, you would not mock us so.
You're right - Gond saved me for a reason.
I've come to free you - I already dealt with some of the Banites.
Take a deep breath - I'm here to help.
You're cowards.
I think they're being held underwater.
I need to destroy the Steel Watch. Are you going to help me or not?
To the tyrants who collared me like a dog and took my daughter? No - I think not.

Synopsis: Toobin asks for the player's help to save the Gondian families and free them from serving the Banites.
